cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper deals with distributed algorithms for information dissemination, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of direct addressing and communication constraints also make it relevant to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The optimization of message and bit complexity may also place it under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of theoretical analysis and lower bounds may also make it relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT).
